arguments.name: hpxml_path
arguments.description: Absolute/relative path of the HPXML file.

arguments.name: weather_dir
arguments.description: Absolute/relative path of the weather directory.

arguments.name: software_program_used
arguments.description: The name of the software program used.

arguments.name: software_program_version
arguments.description: The version of the software program used.

arguments.name: simulation_control_timestep
arguments.description: Value must be a divisor of 60.

arguments.name: simulation_control_run_period_begin_month
arguments.display_name: Simulation Control: Run Period Begin Month
arguments.description: This numeric field should contain the starting month number (1 = January, 2 = February, etc.) for the annual run period desired.

arguments.name: simulation_control_run_period_begin_day_of_month
arguments.display_name: Simulation Control: Run Period Begin Day of Month
arguments.description: This numeric field should contain the starting day of the starting month (must be valid for month) for the annual run period desired.

arguments.name: simulation_control_run_period_end_month
arguments.display_name: Simulation Control: Run Period End Month
arguments.description: This numeric field should contain the end month number (1 = January, 2 = February, etc.) for the annual run period desired.

arguments.name: simulation_control_run_period_end_day_of_month
arguments.display_name: Simulation Control: Run Period End Day of Month
arguments.description: This numeric field should contain the ending day of the ending month (must be valid for month) for the annual run period desired.

arguments.name: simulation_control_daylight_saving_enabled
arguments.description: Whether to use daylight saving.

arguments.name: simulation_control_daylight_saving_begin_month
arguments.display_name: Simulation Control: Daylight Saving Begin Month
arguments.description: This numeric field should contain the starting month number (1 = January, 2 = February, etc.) for the annual daylight saving period desired.

arguments.name: simulation_control_daylight_saving_begin_day_of_month
arguments.display_name: Simulation Control: Daylight Saving Begin Day of Month
arguments.description: This numeric field should contain the starting day of the starting month (must be valid for month) for the daylight saving period desired.

arguments.name: simulation_control_daylight_saving_end_month
arguments.display_name: Simulation Control: Daylight Saving End Month
arguments.description: This numeric field should contain the end month number (1 = January, 2 = February, etc.) for the daylight saving period desired.

arguments.name: simulation_control_daylight_saving_end_day_of_month
arguments.display_name: Simulation Control: Daylight Saving End Day of Month
arguments.description: This numeric field should contain the ending day of the ending month (must be valid for month) for the daylight saving period desired.

arguments.name: schedules_output_path
arguments.description: Absolute (or relative) path of the output schedules file.

arguments.name: weather_station_epw_filepath
arguments.description: Name of the EPW file.

arguments.name: site_type
arguments.description: The type of site.

arguments.name: geometry_unit_type
arguments.description: The type of unit.

arguments.name: geometry_num_units
arguments.description: The number of units in the building. This is required for single-family attached and multi-family - uncategorized buildings.

arguments.name: geometry_cfa
arguments.description: The total floor area of the conditioned space (including any conditioned basement floor area).

arguments.name: geometry_num_floors_above_grade
arguments.description: The number of floors above grade (in the unit if single-family attached, and in the building if multi-family - uncategorized).

arguments.name: geometry_wall_height
arguments.description: The average height of the walls.

arguments.name: geometry_orientation
arguments.description: The house's orientation is measured clockwise from due south when viewed from above (e.g., North=0, East=90, South=180, West=270).

arguments.name: geometry_aspect_ratio
arguments.description: The ratio of the front/back wall length to the left/right wall length, excluding any protruding garage wall area.

arguments.name: geometry_level
arguments.description: The level of the multi-family - uncategorized unit.

arguments.name: geometry_horizontal_location
arguments.description: The horizontal location of the single-family attached or multi-family - uncategorized unit when viewing the front of the building.

arguments.name: geometry_corridor_position
arguments.description: The position of the corridor.

arguments.name: geometry_corridor_width
arguments.description: The width of the corridor.

arguments.name: geometry_inset_width
arguments.description: The width of the inset.

arguments.name: geometry_inset_depth
arguments.description: The depth of the inset.

arguments.name: geometry_inset_position
arguments.description: The position of the inset.

arguments.name: geometry_balcony_depth
arguments.description: The depth of the balcony.

arguments.name: geometry_garage_width
arguments.description: The width of the garage. Enter zero for no garage.

arguments.name: geometry_garage_depth
arguments.description: The depth of the garage.

arguments.name: geometry_garage_protrusion
arguments.description: The fraction of the garage that is protruding from the living space.

arguments.name: geometry_garage_position
arguments.description: The position of the garage.

arguments.name: geometry_foundation_type
arguments.description: The foundation type of the building.

arguments.name: geometry_foundation_height
arguments.description: The height of the foundation (e.g., 3ft for crawlspace, 8ft for basement). Only applies to basements/crawlspaces.

arguments.name: geometry_foundation_height_above_grade
arguments.description: The depth above grade of the foundation wall. Only applies to basements/crawlspaces.

arguments.name: geometry_roof_type
arguments.description: The roof type of the building.

arguments.name: geometry_roof_pitch
arguments.description: The roof pitch of the attic. Ignored if the building has a flat roof.

arguments.name: geometry_roof_structure
arguments.description: The roof structure of the building. Ignored if the building has a flat roof.

arguments.name: geometry_attic_type
arguments.description: The attic type of the building. Ignored if the building has a flat roof.

arguments.name: geometry_eaves_depth
arguments.description: The eaves depth of the roof.

arguments.name: geometry_num_bedrooms
arguments.description: Specify the number of bedrooms. Used to determine the energy usage of appliances and plug loads, hot water usage, etc.

arguments.name: geometry_num_bathrooms
arguments.description: Specify the number of bathrooms.

arguments.name: geometry_num_occupants
arguments.description: Specify the number of occupants. A value of 'auto' will calculate the average number of occupants from the number of bedrooms. Used to specify the internal gains from people only.

arguments.name: floor_assembly_r
arguments.description: Assembly R-value for the floor (foundation ceiling). Ignored if a slab foundation.

arguments.name: foundation_wall_insulation_r
arguments.description: Nominal R-value for the foundation wall insulation. Only applies to basements/crawlspaces.

arguments.name: foundation_wall_insulation_distance_to_top
arguments.display_name: Foundation: Wall Insulation Distance To Top
arguments.description: The distance from the top of the foundation wall to the top of the foundation wall insulation. Only applies to basements/crawlspaces.

arguments.name: foundation_wall_insulation_distance_to_bottom
arguments.display_name: Foundation: Wall Insulation Distance To Bottom
arguments.description: The distance from the top of the foundation wall to the bottom of the foundation wall insulation. Only applies to basements/crawlspaces.

arguments.name: foundation_wall_assembly_r
arguments.description: Assembly R-value for the foundation walls. Only applies to basements/crawlspaces. If provided, overrides the previous foundation wall insulation inputs.

arguments.name: slab_perimeter_insulation_r
arguments.description: Nominal R-value of the vertical slab perimeter insulation. Applies to slab-on-grade foundations and basement/crawlspace floors.

arguments.name: slab_perimeter_depth
arguments.description: Depth from grade to bottom of vertical slab perimeter insulation. Applies to slab-on-grade foundations and basement/crawlspace floors.

arguments.name: slab_under_insulation_r
arguments.display_name: Slab: Under Slab Insulation Nominal R-value
arguments.description: Nominal R-value of the horizontal under slab insulation. Applies to slab-on-grade foundations and basement/crawlspace floors.

arguments.name: slab_under_width
arguments.description: Width from slab edge inward of horizontal under-slab insulation. Enter 999 to specify that the under slab insulation spans the entire slab. Applies to slab-on-grade foundations and basement/crawlspace floors.

arguments.name: slab_carpet_fraction
arguments.description: Fraction of the slab floor area that is carpeted.

arguments.name: slab_carpet_r
arguments.description: R-value of the slab carpet.

arguments.name: ceiling_assembly_r
arguments.description: Assembly R-value for the ceiling (attic floor).

arguments.name: roof_material_type
arguments.description: The material type of the roof.

arguments.name: roof_color
arguments.description: The color of the roof.

arguments.name: roof_assembly_r
arguments.description: Assembly R-value of the roof.

arguments.name: roof_solar_absorptance
arguments.description: The solar absorptance of the roof.

arguments.name: roof_emittance
arguments.description: The emittance of the roof.

arguments.name: roof_radiant_barrier
arguments.description: Specifies whether the attic has a radiant barrier.

arguments.name: neighbor_front_distance
arguments.description: The minimum distance between the simulated house and the neighboring house to the front (not including eaves). A value of zero indicates no neighbors.

arguments.name: neighbor_back_distance
arguments.description: The minimum distance between the simulated house and the neighboring house to the back (not including eaves). A value of zero indicates no neighbors.

arguments.name: neighbor_left_distance
arguments.description: The minimum distance between the simulated house and the neighboring house to the left (not including eaves). A value of zero indicates no neighbors.

arguments.name: neighbor_right_distance
arguments.description: The minimum distance between the simulated house and the neighboring house to the right (not including eaves). A value of zero indicates no neighbors.

arguments.name: neighbor_front_height
arguments.description: The height of the neighboring building to the front. A value of 'auto' will use the same height as this building.

arguments.name: neighbor_back_height
arguments.description: The height of the neighboring building to the back. A value of 'auto' will use the same height as this building.

arguments.name: neighbor_left_height
arguments.description: The height of the neighboring building to the left. A value of 'auto' will use the same height as this building.

arguments.name: neighbor_right_height
arguments.description: The height of the neighboring building to the right. A value of 'auto' will use the same height as this building.

arguments.name: wall_type
arguments.description: The type of exterior walls.

arguments.name: wall_siding_type
arguments.description: The siding type of the exterior walls.

arguments.name: wall_color
arguments.description: The color of the exterior walls.

arguments.name: wall_assembly_r
arguments.description: Assembly R-value of the exterior walls.

arguments.name: wall_solar_absorptance
arguments.description: The solar absorptance of the exterior walls.

arguments.name: wall_emittance
arguments.description: The emittance of the exterior walls.

arguments.name: window_front_wwr
arguments.description: The ratio of window area to wall area for the building's front facade. Enter 0 if specifying Front Window Area instead.

arguments.name: window_back_wwr
arguments.description: The ratio of window area to wall area for the building's back facade. Enter 0 if specifying Back Window Area instead.

arguments.name: window_left_wwr
arguments.description: The ratio of window area to wall area for the building's left facade. Enter 0 if specifying Left Window Area instead.

arguments.name: window_right_wwr
arguments.description: The ratio of window area to wall area for the building's right facade. Enter 0 if specifying Right Window Area instead.

arguments.name: window_area_front
arguments.description: The amount of window area on the building's front facade. Enter 0 if specifying Front Window-to-Wall Ratio instead.

arguments.name: window_area_back
arguments.description: The amount of window area on the building's back facade. Enter 0 if specifying Back Window-to-Wall Ratio instead.

arguments.name: window_area_left
arguments.description: The amount of window area on the building's left facade. Enter 0 if specifying Left Window-to-Wall Ratio instead.

arguments.name: window_area_right
arguments.description: The amount of window area on the building's right facade. Enter 0 if specifying Right Window-to-Wall Ratio instead.

arguments.name: window_aspect_ratio
arguments.description: Ratio of window height to width.

arguments.name: window_fraction_operable
arguments.description: Fraction of windows that are operable.

arguments.name: window_ufactor
arguments.description: The heat transfer coefficient of the windows.

arguments.name: window_shgc
arguments.description: The ratio of solar heat gain through a glazing system compared to that of an unobstructed opening, for windows.

arguments.name: window_interior_shading_winter
arguments.description: Interior shading multiplier for the heating season. 1.0 indicates no reduction in solar gain, 0.85 indicates 15% reduction, etc.

arguments.name: window_interior_shading_summer
arguments.description: Interior shading multiplier for the cooling season. 1.0 indicates no reduction in solar gain, 0.85 indicates 15% reduction, etc.

arguments.name: overhangs_front_depth
arguments.description: Specifies the depth of overhangs for windows on the front facade.

arguments.name: overhangs_front_distance_to_top_of_window
arguments.display_name: Overhangs: Front Facade Distance to Top of Window
arguments.description: Specifies the distance to the top of window of overhangs for windows on the front facade.

arguments.name: overhangs_back_depth
arguments.description: Specifies the depth of overhangs for windows on the back facade.

arguments.name: overhangs_back_distance_to_top_of_window
arguments.display_name: Overhangs: Back Facade Distance to Top of Window
arguments.description: Specifies the distance to the top of window of overhangs for windows on the back facade.

arguments.name: overhangs_left_depth
arguments.description: Specifies the depth of overhangs for windows on the left facade.

arguments.name: overhangs_left_distance_to_top_of_window
arguments.display_name: Overhangs: Left Facade Distance to Top of Window
arguments.description: Specifies the distance to the top of window of overhangs for windows on the left facade.

arguments.name: overhangs_right_depth
arguments.description: Specifies the depth of overhangs for windows on the right facade.

arguments.name: overhangs_right_distance_to_top_of_window
arguments.display_name: Overhangs: Right Facade Distance to Top of Window
arguments.description: Specifies the distance to the top of window of overhangs for windows on the right facade.

arguments.name: skylight_area_front
arguments.description: The amount of skylight area on the building's front conditioned roof facade.

arguments.name: skylight_area_back
arguments.description: The amount of skylight area on the building's back conditioned roof facade.

arguments.name: skylight_area_left
arguments.description: The amount of skylight area on the building's left conditioned roof facade.

arguments.name: skylight_area_right
arguments.description: The amount of skylight area on the building's right conditioned roof facade.

arguments.name: skylight_ufactor
arguments.description: The heat transfer coefficient of the skylights.

arguments.name: skylight_shgc
arguments.description: The ratio of solar heat gain through a glazing system compared to that of an unobstructed opening, for skylights.

arguments.name: door_area
arguments.description: The area of the opaque door(s).

arguments.name: door_rvalue
arguments.description: R-value of the doors.

arguments.name: air_leakage_units
arguments.description: The unit of measure for the above-grade living air leakage.

arguments.name: air_leakage_value
arguments.description: Air exchange rate, in ACH or CFM at 50 Pascals.

arguments.name: air_leakage_shelter_coefficient
arguments.description: The local shelter coefficient (AIM-2 infiltration model) accounts for nearby buildings, trees, and obstructions.

arguments.name: heating_system_type
arguments.description: The type of heating system. Use 'none' if there is no heating system.

arguments.name: heating_system_fuel
arguments.description: The fuel type of the heating system. Ignored for ElectricResistance.

arguments.name: heating_system_heating_efficiency
arguments.display_name: Heating System: Rated AFUE or Percent
arguments.description: The rated heating efficiency value of the heating system.

arguments.name: heating_system_heating_capacity
arguments.description: The output heating capacity of the heating system. If using 'auto', the autosizing algorithm will use ACCA Manual J/S to set the capacity to meet its load served.

arguments.name: heating_system_fraction_heat_load_served
arguments.display_name: Heating System: Fraction Heat Load Served
arguments.description: The heating load served by the heating system.

arguments.name: heating_system_electric_auxiliary_energy
arguments.description: The electric auxiliary energy of the heating system.

arguments.name: cooling_system_type
arguments.description: The type of cooling system. Use 'none' if there is no cooling system.

arguments.name: cooling_system_cooling_efficiency_seer
arguments.description: The rated efficiency value of the central air conditioner cooling system.

arguments.name: cooling_system_cooling_efficiency_eer
arguments.description: The rated efficiency value of the room air conditioner cooling system.

arguments.name: cooling_system_cooling_compressor_type
arguments.description: The compressor type of the cooling system. Only applies to central air conditioner.

arguments.name: cooling_system_cooling_sensible_heat_fraction
arguments.display_name: Cooling System: Cooling Sensible Heat Fraction
arguments.description: The sensible heat fraction of the cooling system. Ignored for evaporative cooler.

arguments.name: cooling_system_cooling_capacity
arguments.description: The output cooling capacity of the cooling system. If using 'auto', the autosizing algorithm will use ACCA Manual J/S to set the capacity to meet its load served. Ignored for evaporative cooler.

arguments.name: cooling_system_fraction_cool_load_served
arguments.display_name: Cooling System: Fraction Cool Load Served
arguments.description: The cooling load served by the cooling system.

arguments.name: cooling_system_evap_cooler_is_ducted
arguments.display_name: Cooling System: Evaporative Cooler Is Ducted
arguments.description: Whether the evaporative cooler is ducted or not. Only used for evaporative cooler.

arguments.name: heat_pump_type
arguments.description: The type of heat pump. Use 'none' if there is no heat pump.

arguments.name: heat_pump_heating_efficiency_hspf
arguments.description: The rated heating efficiency value of the air-to-air/mini-split heat pump.

arguments.name: heat_pump_heating_efficiency_cop
arguments.description: The rated heating efficiency value of the ground-to-air heat pump.

arguments.name: heat_pump_cooling_efficiency_seer
arguments.description: The rated cooling efficiency value of the air-to-air/mini-split heat pump.

arguments.name: heat_pump_cooling_efficiency_eer
arguments.description: The rated cooling efficiency value of the ground-to-air heat pump.

arguments.name: heat_pump_cooling_compressor_type
arguments.description: The compressor type of the heat pump. Only applies to air-to-air and mini-split.

arguments.name: heat_pump_cooling_sensible_heat_fraction
arguments.display_name: Heat Pump: Cooling Sensible Heat Fraction
arguments.description: The sensible heat fraction of the heat pump.

arguments.name: heat_pump_heating_capacity
arguments.description: The output heating capacity of the heat pump. If using 'auto', the autosizing algorithm will use ACCA Manual J/S to set the capacity to meet its load served.

arguments.name: heat_pump_heating_capacity_17F
arguments.description: The output heating capacity of the heat pump at 17F. Only applies to air-to-air and mini-split.

arguments.name: heat_pump_cooling_capacity
arguments.description: The output cooling capacity of the heat pump. If using 'auto', the autosizing algorithm will use ACCA Manual J/S to set the capacity to meet its load served.

arguments.name: heat_pump_fraction_heat_load_served
arguments.display_name: Heat Pump: Fraction Heat Load Served
arguments.description: The heating load served by the heat pump.

arguments.name: heat_pump_fraction_cool_load_served
arguments.display_name: Heat Pump: Fraction Cool Load Served
arguments.description: The cooling load served by the heat pump.

arguments.name: heat_pump_backup_fuel
arguments.description: The backup fuel type of the heat pump. Use 'none' if there is no backup heating.

arguments.name: heat_pump_backup_heating_efficiency
arguments.description: The backup rated efficiency value of the heat pump. Percent for electricity fuel type. AFUE otherwise.

arguments.name: heat_pump_backup_heating_capacity
arguments.description: The backup output heating capacity of the heat pump. If using 'auto', the autosizing algorithm will use ACCA Manual J/S to set the capacity to meet its load served.

arguments.name: heat_pump_backup_heating_switchover_temp
arguments.display_name: Heat Pump: Backup Heating Switchover Temperature
arguments.description: The temperature at which the heat pump stops operating and the backup heating system starts running. Only applies to air-to-air and mini-split.

arguments.name: heat_pump_mini_split_is_ducted
arguments.description: Whether the mini-split heat pump is ducted or not.

arguments.name: water_heater_type
arguments.description: The type of water heater. Use 'none' if there is no water heater.

arguments.name: water_heater_fuel_type
arguments.description: The fuel type of water heater. Ignored for heat pump water heater.

arguments.name: water_heater_location
arguments.description: The location of water heater.

arguments.name: water_heater_tank_volume
arguments.description: Nominal volume of water heater tank. Set to auto to have volume autosized. Only applies to storage water heater, heat pump water heater, and space-heating boiler with storage tank.

arguments.name: water_heater_heating_capacity
arguments.description: The maximum energy input rating of water heater. Set to auto to have this field autosized. Only applies to storage water heater.

arguments.name: water_heater_efficiency_type
arguments.description: The efficiency type of water heater. Does not apply to space-heating boilers.

arguments.name: water_heater_efficiency_ef
arguments.description: Ratio of useful energy output from water heater to the total amount of energy delivered from the water heater.

arguments.name: water_heater_efficiency_uef
arguments.description: The uniform energy factor of water heater. Does not apply to space-heating boilers.

arguments.name: water_heater_recovery_efficiency
arguments.description: Ratio of energy delivered to water heater to the energy content of the fuel consumed by the water heater. Only used for non-electric storage water heaters.

arguments.name: water_heater_standby_loss
arguments.description: The standby loss of water heater. Only applies to space-heating boilers.

arguments.name: water_heater_jacket_rvalue
arguments.description: The jacket R-value of water heater. Doesn't apply to instantaneous water heater or space-heating boiler with tankless coil.

arguments.name: water_heater_setpoint_temperature
arguments.description: The setpoint temperature of water heater.

arguments.name: dhw_distribution_system_type
arguments.description: The type of the hot water distribution system.

arguments.name: dhw_distribution_standard_piping_length
arguments.display_name: Hot Water Distribution: Standard Piping Length
arguments.description: If the distribution system is Standard, the length of the piping. A value of 'auto' will use a default.

arguments.name: dhw_distribution_recirc_control_type
arguments.display_name: Hot Water Distribution: Recirculation Control Type
arguments.description: If the distribution system is Recirculation, the type of hot water recirculation control, if any.

arguments.name: dhw_distribution_recirc_piping_length
arguments.display_name: Hot Water Distribution: Recirculation Piping Length
arguments.description: If the distribution system is Recirculation, the length of the recirculation piping.

arguments.name: dhw_distribution_recirc_branch_piping_length
arguments.display_name: Hot Water Distribution: Recirculation Branch Piping Length
arguments.description: If the distribution system is Recirculation, the length of the recirculation branch piping.

arguments.name: dhw_distribution_recirc_pump_power
arguments.display_name: Hot Water Distribution: Recirculation Pump Power
arguments.description: If the distribution system is Recirculation, the recirculation pump power.

arguments.name: dhw_distribution_pipe_r
arguments.display_name: Hot Water Distribution: Pipe Insulation Nominal R-Value
arguments.description: Nominal R-value of the pipe insulation.

arguments.name: dwhr_facilities_connected
arguments.display_name: Drain Water Heat Recovery: Facilities Connected
arguments.description: Which facilities are connected for the drain water heat recovery. Use 'none' if there is no drawin water heat recovery system.

arguments.name: dwhr_equal_flow
arguments.display_name: Drain Water Heat Recovery: Equal Flow
